  <name>SubtitlePlayer</name>
  <summary>Professional video player with subtitle download and AI generation</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      SubtitlePlayer is a powerful, feature-rich video player for Linux that makes
      working with subtitles effortless. Whether you need to download subtitles from
      OpenSubtitles.org or generate them automatically using AI, SubtitlePlayer has you covered.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Play videos in all major formats (MP4, AVI, MKV, MOV, WMV, FLV, WebM)</li>
      <li>Download subtitles from OpenSubtitles.org database</li>
      <li>AI-powered subtitle generation using OpenAI Whisper (supports 99+ languages)</li>
      <li>Extensive subtitle customization (font, size, color, position, timing)</li>
      <li>Click-to-seek timeline for quick navigation</li>
      <li>Right-click context menu for instant access to all features</li>
      <li>Double-click fullscreen toggle</li>
      <li>Per-video subtitle preferences that persist</li>
      <li>Modern, professional PyQt6 interface</li>
      <li>Keyboard shortcuts for power users</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Perfect for language learners, accessibility needs, content creators, and anyone
      who wants a better video watching experience with complete subtitle control.
    </p>
  </description>
  
